Smothered under all this swirl of negativity is another worrying story – financing university education.
Public universities, particularly the larger ones, are struggling under humongous debt that university councils and managements see no easy solution to. 
The reason universities are in this uncomfortable situation are well known. Up to about six or so years ago, government capitation (the money that government gives to universities to run those institutions) was not great but fees from parallel programmes offered to self-sponsored students more than made up for any shortfalls. 



